            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_51gc' title='Col. 51GC &mdash; HL Deb 24 June 2002 vol 636 c51GC' name='column_51gc' href='#column_51gc' rel='bookmark'>51GC</a>
            authorities, given that education authorities, housing authorities, and PCTs will only ever come into the adoption process for one small part of it. As a result of our discussion, I am more convinced than I was before of the need for co-ordination and an access point to which someone who is involved in the adoption process can go, if only to find out the next place where they need to go.
          </p>
